<% content_for :title, "Cookie Policy" %>

<article class="prose-legal">
  <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
  <p class="doc-meta">Effective date: June 1, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; Veridion Studios Ltd.</p>

  <p>This policy explains how Tessera uses cookies and similar technologies when you visit our platform.</p>

  <h2>1. What are cookies</h2>
  <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser when you visit a website. They allow us to remember information about your visit, such as your login session.</p>

  <h2>2. Cookies we use</h2>

  <h3>Strictly necessary</h3>
  <p>These cookies are required for the platform to function and cannot be disabled:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>_tessera_session</strong> — maintains your login session. Expires at end of session or 2 weeks if you choose "remember me".</li>
    <li><strong>_csrf_token</strong> — protects against cross-site request forgery attacks.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Functional</h3>
  <p>These cookies remember your preferences:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>dashboard_role</strong> — remembers whether you last used the developer or client dashboard.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Third-party</h3>
  <p>These cookies are set by our service providers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — fraud prevention and payment processing. Stripe may set cookies such as <code>__stripe_mid</code> and <code>__stripe_sid</code>. See <a href="https://stripe.com/cookies-policy/legal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stripe's cookie policy</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Sentry</strong> — error tracking. Sentry may set session identifiers to correlate error reports. See <a href="https://sentry.io/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Sentry's privacy policy</a>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Managing cookies</h2>
  <p>You can control cookies through your browser settings. Disabling strictly necessary cookies will prevent you from logging into Tessera. Most browsers allow you to view and delete cookies via their privacy settings.</p>

  <h2>4. Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about our use of cookies: <strong>privacy@veridion.studio</strong>.</p>
</article>